Federal-Mogul Holdings LLC Key Developments

Federal-Mogul Holdings LLC Files Form 15
Feb 24 17
Federal-Mogul Holdings LLC has announced that it has filed a Form 15 with the Securities and Exchange Commission to voluntarily deregister its common stock under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended. The par value of the company's common stock was $0.01 per share.


Federal-Mogul Holdings LLC Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Full Year Ended December 31, 2016
Feb 23 17
Federal-Mogul Holdings LLC reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the fourth quarter and full year ended December 31, 2016. For the quarter, the company reported net sales of $1,788 million compared to $1,798 million a year ago. Operating income was $47 million compared to operating loss of $42 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations before income taxes was $27 million compared to loss from continuing operations before income taxes of $58 million a year ago. Net income attributable to the company was $1 million or $0.01 per basic and diluted share compared to net loss attributable to the company of $58 million or $0.35 per basic and diluted share a year ago. EBITDA was $162 million compared to $64 million a year ago. Adjusted net income from continuing operations was $16 million compared to $37 million a year ago.



For the year, the company reported net sales of $7,434 million compared to $7,419 million a year ago. Operating income was $231 million compared to $1 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations before income taxes was $145 million compared to loss from continuing operations before income taxes of $81 million a year ago. Net income attributable to the company was $82 million or $0.49 per basic and diluted share compared to net loss attributable to the company of $110 million or $0.67 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net cash provided from operating activities was $546 million compared to $38 million a year ago. Expenditures for property, plant and equipment was $381 million compared to $440 million a year ago. EBITDA was $665 million compared to $405 million a year ago. Adjusted net income from continuing operations was $141 million compared to $114 million a year ago.


Federal-Mogul Holdings LLC Announces Executive Changes
Feb 16 17
Federal-Mogul Holdings LLC announced the appointment of Bradley S. Norton as co-chief executive officer of the company and chief executive officer of its Motorparts division, effective March 8, 2017. Rainer Jueckstock will remain as co-chief executive officer of Federal-Mogul Holdings LLC and CEO of Federal-Mogul Powertrain. Norton has more than 25 years of global automotive experience in both original equipment and the aftermarket. He joined Federal-Mogul Motorparts in 2014 as senior vice president and general manager, chassis & service. Norton succeeds Daniel A. Ninivaggi, who had served as co-CEO and CEO of Federal-Mogul Motorparts since 2014.


