Federal-Mogul Holdings Corp. Federal-Mogul Abex RX 6297 lining in Brake System

































































        Home
    

        Drivetrains
    

        Brake System
    

        Federal-Mogul Abex RX 6297 Brake Lining
    










        Federal-Mogul Abex RX 6297 Brake Lining
    



        The Federal-Mogul Abex RX 6297 brake lining helps is capable of delivering a stopping distance of 217 ft. from 60 mph when used on a loaded truck with a 23,000 lb. drive axle.
    




        Federal-Mogul Holdings Corp.
    



        May 6, 2016
    
































































Federal-Mogul Motorparts, a division of Federal-Mogul Holdings Corp., has expanded its range of Abex Reduced Stopping Distance (RSD) certified commercial grade friction linings to include the Abex RX 6297 lining.

Provides excellent lining and drum wear
Exceeds both the Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standards (FMVSS) 121 Reduced Stopping Distance (RSD) requirement and OE brake manufacturer standard for 23,000-lb. (10,432.62 kg) tractor applications
Capable of delivering stopping distance of just 217 ft. (66.14 m) from 60 mph (96.56 kmh) on a tractor equipped with a 23,000-pound drive axle and 14,600-pound steer axle under loaded conditions, beating FMVSS 121 RSD standard and OE brake manufacturer requirement of 250 and 225 ft. (76.2 and 68.58 m), respectively
Copper-free, crack-resistant lining engineered to help maintain like-new braking performance while experiencing minimal swell and growth
Meets FMVSS requirements through use of advanced non-asbestos organic (NAO), semi-metallic and combination NAO/semi-met formulations that produce required brake torque to stop under 250 ft. (76.2 m)

 
 




